<section
  id="about"
  class="py-16 lg:py-24"
  aria-labelledby="about-heading"
>
  <div class="max-w-site mx-auto px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-main">

      <p class="eyebrow mb-4">About</p>
      <h2
        id="about-heading"
        class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold mb-8"
        style="color: var(--color-text-primary); letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
      >
        14+ years shipping systems at scale
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-5 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
        <p>
          I'm a backend-focused engineer who enjoys building systems that operate reliably at scale.
          Over the past 14+ years I've worked across distributed platforms, ML-powered data pipelines,
          and full-stack products &mdash; with a particular interest in system architecture, developer
          experience, and making complex systems easier to operate.
        </p>
        <p>
          Currently I work at <span style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">PAR Technology</span> building
          backend infrastructure for Chevron's fuel retail ecosystem. The platform powers mobile apps and
          digital services used by millions of customers. My work focuses on transaction processing, loyalty
          systems, and developer tooling. One recent improvement was introducing
          <span style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">.NET Aspire</span> to our local development
          environment, simplifying multi-service startup and significantly improving developer productivity.
        </p>
        <p>
          Previously I spent four years at <span style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Strategic Vision</span> building
          analytics platforms for the automotive industry. I worked on systems that processed large-scale
          consumer survey data, including NLP pipelines for analyzing free-text and voice responses, and
          real-time visualization tools used by major automotive manufacturers.
        </p>
        <p>
          I also co-founded <span style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">LetMePark</span>, where I
          served as CTO and built the platform from the ground up. The system connected drivers with parking
          facilities and grew to operate across hundreds of locations in Spain and over a thousand across Europe.
        </p>
        <p>
          I consider myself a software engineer rather than a language specialist. While most of my work has
          been in <span style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">.NET and Azure</span>, I've also shipped
          systems using Node.js, React, Angular, iOS, and machine learning pipelines when the problem required it.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm particularly interested in distributed systems, developer tooling, and the practical application
          of AI in engineering workflows. My day-to-day toolkit includes
          <span style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Cursor, Claude Code, GitHub Copilot, Codex</span>,
          and local LLM tooling such as Ollama and LM Studio.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside of work I enjoy basketball, board games (especially
          <span style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Terraforming Mars</span>), and experimenting with
          new developer tools and technologies.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
